    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a museum-grade example of Hiroshima\u2019s sequential twin-turbocharged masterpiece. The 13B-REW rotary engine maintains factory-spec compression across both rotors, delivering seamless boost transition through the complex vacuum-controlled solenoid network. Power is delivered via a precise 5-speed short-throw manual to a Torsen limited-slip differential. The lightweight front-midship chassis retains its original double-wishbone suspension geometry, offering telepathic turn-in and a near-perfect 50:50 weight distribution. Finished in its original paint with a flawless undercarriage and no aftermarket modifications, this specimen represents the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering.",
